Description: Two joining fragments of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The impressions at the rear are flat and slightly concave, there are impressions of lines from fibres of some kind plants (basket or wood?), turned string impressions in the break and also on the top. The side shows few finger impressions. The top bears a part of a seal-impression with an ornamental design in form of half circles at the edge and oval interlacing lines in the middle.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
Additional IDs: Excavation/small finds number: S74 + S86 (Excavation Number)
